I'm running into the following issue while trying to make our add-on compatible with Confluence 6.0.

The add-on defines a macro that looks like this:

{code}
public class LucidXHtmlMacro implements Macro, EditorImagePlaceholder, ResourceAware {

    public LucidXHtmlMacro(/** ... */) {
    }

    public BodyType getBodyType() {
        return BodyType.NONE;
    }

    public OutputType getOutputType() {
        return OutputType.BLOCK;
    }

    @Override
    public String execute(Map<String, String> params, String body, ConversionContext cc) throws MacroExecutionException {
        if (!(cc instanceof DefaultConversionContext)){
            return "";
        }

        // render macro contents...
    }

    @Override
    public ImagePlaceholder getImagePlaceholder(Map<String, String> params, ConversionContext cc) {
        // image attachment file name to use as placeholder
        String name = params.get("name");   
        ContentEntityObject page = null;
        PageContext pageContext = cc.getPageContext();
        page = pageContext.getEntity();

        macroUtil.setContext(params,page);

        System.out.println("getImagePlaceholder, name = " + name);
        Attachment attachment = attachmentManager.getAttachment(page, name);
        System.out.println("getImagePlaceholder, page = " + page);
        System.out.println("getImagePlaceholder, attachment = " + attachment);

        String url = attachment.getDownloadPathWithoutVersion();

        if (url != null) {
            return new DefaultImagePlaceholder(url, new Dimensions(macroUtil.getWidth(), macroUtil.getHeight()), true);
        }
        else {
            return new DefaultImagePlaceholder(IMAGE_PATH, new Dimensions(114, 114), true);
        }
    }
}
{code}

Before a macro is inserted, the add-on creates an image attachment on the current page that is then used as a placeholder macro.

This code works fine in pre-6.0, however something breaks in 6.0:
* I can see the placeholder image immediately after the macro is inserted
* However, when I save the page and edit it again, the placeholder isn't there

I did some debugging and looks like now when I open the page editor, it loads a draft that's different from the original page. See log statements below:

After editing a page and inserting our macro into it:

{code}
[INFO] [talledLocalContainer] getImagePlaceholder, name = 2-Circle Venn Diagram-1391-66816528-0.png
[INFO] [talledLocalContainer] getImagePlaceholder, page = page: New page v.4 (950274)
[INFO] [talledLocalContainer] getImagePlaceholder, attachment = Attachment: 2-Circle Venn Diagram-1391-66816528-0.png v.1 (950296) admin
{code}

After saving and editing the page again:
{code}
[INFO] [talledLocalContainer] getImagePlaceholder, name = 2-Circle Venn Diagram-1391-66816528-0.png
[INFO] [talledLocalContainer] getImagePlaceholder, page = page: New page v.1 (950275)
[INFO] [talledLocalContainer] getImagePlaceholder, attachment = null
{code}

Note that the second time the page id and version is different, and for some reason the attachment is missing (although the attachment is still there on the original page, viewable from the GUI, with exact same name). 

So it looks like somehow the draft that gets initialized from the original page loses the reference to the original page's attachments.

Is this a bug or do I need to change my code to somehow retrieve the original page when I want to read/write attachments?

I am currently blocked on this.

