If a JIRA issue is created from a Task List item in confluence, it would be nice if the the completion could be related.  If the assignee closes the issue in JIRA, it would be nice if the check box in Confluence were checked off.  If multiple issues are created from the same Task List item, perhaps all issues would need to be closed before the Task List item is complete.

If the user goes in Confluence and looks at his/her tasks, it shows up as open even if the JIRA issue was closed.

Current "workaround" is to convert that Task List item to a bullet list and create two macros to list all open Task List items and all open JIRA Issues on a single Confluence page.

